
[1]recondite

   REC'ONDITE, a. [L. reconditus, recondo; re and condo to conceal.]

   1. Secret; hidden from the view or intellect; abstruse; as recondite
   causes of things.

   2. Profound; dealing in things abstruse; as recondite studies.
